 WHITE RIVER: The SPCA Car Boot Sale, held on Saturday at Casterbridge Lifestyle Centre, gave locals the chance to not only help out the White River SPCA, but also to get rid of some white elephants in their homes. The rest of their profits were their own to keep.This is a monthly event which takes place the first Saturday of every month. It costs R100 to book your spot at the market. Interested exhibitors can phone Estelle de Villiers on 083-664-7505. ALSO READ: Pets should receive first priority this festive season, says SPCA